# Jitsi Configuration
# Using the official public Jitsi server (NO API TOKEN NEEDED!)
# 
# For more info: https://jitsi.org/
# Docs: https://github.com/jitsi/jitsi-meet/blob/master/doc/api.md
#
# Note: meet.jit.si is free and public. For production, consider:
# - Jitsi as a Service: https://jaas.8x8.vc
# - Self-hosted: https://jitsi.org/downloads/

VITE_JITSI_DOMAIN=meet.jit.si
VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Meeting room names are auto-generated based on case ID and user IDs
# Example rooms created: lexconnect-case1-1-2, lexconnect-case2-1-3, etc.
# Each room is unique and temporary.
